lf%20of%20Americans%20plan%20to%20give%20them%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Retail%20Federation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20will%20remain%20unspent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGift%20cards%20get%20lost%20or%20forgotten%2C%20or%20recipients%20hang%20on%20to%20them%20for%20a%20special%20occasion.%20In%20a%20July%20survey%2C%20the%20consumer%20finance%20company%20Bankrate%20found%20that%2047%25%20of%20U.S.%20adults%20had%20at%20least%20one%20unspent%20gift%20card%20or%20voucher%20with%20an%20average%20value%20of%20%24187.%20That's%20a%20total%20of%20%2423%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20gift%20of%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20a%20federal%20law%20that%20went%20into%20effect%20in%202010%2C%20a%20gift%20card%20can't%20expire%20for%20five%20years%20from%20the%20time%20it%20was%20purchased%20or%20from%20the%20last%20time%20someone%20added%20money%20to%20it.%20Some%20state%20laws%20require%20an%20even%20longer%20period.%20In%20New%20York%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20any%20gift%20card%20purchased%20after%20Dec.%2010%2C%202022%2C%20can't%20expire%20for%20nine%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiffering%20state%20laws%20are%20one%20reason%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fgifts%2Ftarget-gift-card%23faqs-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20stores%20have%20stopped%20using%20expiration%20dates%3C%2Fa%3E%20altogether%2C%20says%20Ted%20Rossman%2C%20a%20senior%20industry%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUse%20it%20or%20lose%20it%20%E2%80%A6%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20may%20take%20gift%20cards%20years%20to%20expire%2C%20experts%20say%20it's%20still%20wise%20to%20spend%20them%20quickly.%20Some%20cards%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20generic%20cash%20cards%20from%20Visa%20or%20MasterCard%20%E2%80%94%20will%20start%20accruing%20inactivity%20fees%20if%20they're%20not%20used%20for%20a%20year%2C%20which%20eats%20away%20at%20their%20value.%20Inflation%20also%20makes%20cards%20less%20valuable%20over%20time.%20And%20if%20a%20retail%20store%20closes%20or%20goes%20bankrupt%2C%20a%20gift%20card%20could%20be%20worthless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20consider%20clearing%20out%20your%20stash%20on%20National%20Use%20Your%20Gift%20Card%20Day%2C%20a%20five-year-old%20holiday%20created%20by%20a%20public%20relations%20executive%20and%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fuseyourgiftcard.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebacked%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20multiple%20retailers.%20The%20next%20one%20is%20January%2020%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%E2%80%A6%20or%20sell%20it%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20gift%20card%20you%20don't%20want%2C%20one%20option%20is%20to%20sell%20it%20on%20a%20site%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fcardcash-an-acquisition-of-rde-inc-has-joined-livestream-social-shopping-platform-market-live-1032897346%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECardCash%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Raise.%20Rossman%20says%20resale%20sites%20won't%20give%20you%20face%20value%20for%20your%20cards%2C%20but%20they%20will%20typically%20give%2070%20to%2080%20cents%20per%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20money%20trail%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20happens%20to%20the%20money%20when%20a%20gift%20card%20goes%20unused%3F%20It%20depends%20on%20the%20state%20where%20the%20retailer%20is%20incorporated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20a%20gift%20card%2C%20a%20retailer%20can%20use%20that%20money%20right%20away.%20But%20it%20also%20becomes%20a%20liability%3B%20the%20retailer%20has%20to%20plan%20for%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20gift%20card%20will%20be%20redeemed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20big%20companies%20calculate%20%26quot%3Bbreakage%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20the%20amount%20of%20gift%20card%20liability%20they%20believe%20won't%20be%20redeemed%20based%20on%20historical%20averages.%20For%20some%20companies%2C%20like%20Seattle-based%20Starbucks%2C%20breakage%20is%20a%20huge%20profit-driver.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-