20Act%20read%20thus%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAct%203%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EScene%201%3A%20Joseph%20and%20Mary%20on%20way%20to%20Bethlehem.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EScene%202%3A%20Joseph%20gets%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20police%20on%20false%20charges%20of%20possessing%20drugs%20and%20is%20thrown%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EScene%203%3A%20There%2C%20he%20meets%20Noah%20who%20has%20been%20incarcerated%20for%20attempting%20to%20build%20a%20boat%20without%20a%20proper%20license.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20for%20an%20Indian%20audience%2C%20man.%20Needs%20a%20little%20masala%2C%20you%20know%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20chuckled%20as%20he%20introduced%20us%20to%20the%20actors%20in%20his%20ensemble.%20Inmates%20of%20various%20nationalities%2C%20some%20undertrials%20and%20others%2C%20convicts%2C%20were%20chosen%20to%20play%20the%20roles%20of%20the%20kings%2C%20the%20shepherds%20and%20the%20angels.%20A%20short%2C%20stocky%20Nigerian%20was%20selected%20to%20play%20Joseph.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20finally%20asked%20Nigel%20the%20question%20that%20had%20been%20bothering%20me%20from%20the%20time%20we%20first%20heard%20about%20this%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20are%20you%20doing%20to%20pull%20off%20a%20Christmas%20play%20without%20a%20Mary%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Nigel%20didn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20to%20see%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20a%20Mary%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20responded%20cheerily%20and%20introduced%20us%20to%20a%20tall%2C%20bald%2C%20unsmiling%20Dutchman.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ll%20put%20a%20shawl%20and%20a%20lipstick%20on%20him.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20worst%20fear%20had%20just%20been%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERehearsals%20were%20held%20for%20the%20play%20every%20morning%20and%20every%20evening%20for%202%20weeks.%20Also%20part%20of%20the%20play%20were%20Christmas%20carols%20to%20be%20performed%20by%20a