he%20narrator-translator.%20There%20are%20things%20I%20have%20done%20years%20ago%20which%20still%20bring%20a%20smile%20to%20my%20face.%20Helping%20Nigel%20organize%20his%20play%20is%20one%20of%20them.%20Being%20his%20running%20translator%20is%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20play%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20I%20had%20believed%20till%20that%20point%20that%20two%20thousand%20prisoners%20were%20going%20to%20watch%20a%20Christmas%20play%20performed%20by%20foreign%20inmates%20in%20respectful%20and%20appreciative%20silence%20I%20still%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%20But%20the%20moment%20%E2%80%98Mary%E2%80%99%20walked%20on%20to%20the%20stage%2C%20I%20realized%20respect%20and%20silence%20were%20not%20going%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%2C%20if%20you%20recall%2C%20was%20a%20tall%2C%20bald%20Dutchman.%20Dressed%20in%20a%20red%20saree%2C%20head%20covered%20by%20a%20brown%20shawl%2C%20and%20sporting%20a%20bright%20red%20bindi%20and%20even%20brighter%20lipstick%2C%20he%20looked%20grotesque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CJe%20kaun%20hai%20be%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%E2%80%9CWho%20the%20heck%20is%20that%3F%E2%80%9D)%20asked%20an%20inmate%20sitting%20in%20the%20front%20row%20in%20coarse%20Haryanvi%20in%20a%20stage%20whisper%20loud%20enough%20to%20be%20heard%20by%20at%20least%20thirty%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CManne%20toh%20vilayeti%20kinnar%20lage!%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E(%E2%80%9CLooks%20like%20a%20foreign%20eunuch%20to%20me.%E2%80%9D)%20responded%20his%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20not%20going%20as%20expected.%20And%20it%20was%20just%20the%20beginning.%20Jail%20No.%204%20was%20about%20to%20witness%20the%20most%20unintentionally%20funny%20comedy%20they%20had%20ever%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENigel%20narrated%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20town%20of%20Nazareth%20lived%20a%20young%20woman%20called%20Mary.%20Mary%20had%20found%20favour%20with%20God.%20One%20night%20as%20she%20was%20sleeping%2C%20an%20angel%20entered%20the%20room.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20translated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20angel%20%E2%80%98Gabriel%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20jovial%20Italian%20walked%20onto%20stage%20with%20a%20decidedly%20un-angelic%20swagger.%20He%20stood%20over%20Mary%2C%20stretched%20out%20his%20arms%2C%20and%20announced%20in%20a%20singsong%20voice%2C%20%E2%80%9CHail%20Mary%2C%20full%20of%20grace%2C%20the%20Lord%20is%20with%20you!%20You%20are%20going%20to%20blessed%20with%20a%20son%20who%20will%20be%20known%20as%20the%20Saviour%20of%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%2C%20expressing%20appropriate%20awe%2C%20replied%20in%20thick%20Dutch%20accented%20English%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20how%20can%20this%20be%2C%20seeing%20I%20have%20never%20known%20a%20man%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20did%20not%20bother%20to%20translate%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20play%20progressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20(in%20deep%20voice)%3A%20%E2%80%9CHey%2C%20Mary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%20(in%20equally%20deep%20voice)%3A%20%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20Joseph%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20(in%20deep%20voice)%3A%20%E2%80%9CBethlehem%20is%20crowded.%20All%20the%20inns%20are%20full.%20What%20are%20we%20going%20to%20do%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%3A%20(in%20equally%20deep%20voice)%20%E2%80%9CPlease%2C%20we%20have%20to%20find%20a%20room.%20I%20am%20going%20to%20give%20birth.%20The%20baby%20is%20about%20to%20come.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20audience%20dissolved%20in%20peals%20of%20laughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20Baby%20Jesus%20(a%20cloth%20doll)%20was%20about%20to%20come%20into%20the%20world%2C%20Joseph%20knelt%20beside%20Mary%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CCome%20on%2C%20Mary%2C%20push!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%20I%20heard%20someone%20in%20the%20audience%20mimicking%20a%20baby%E2%80%99s%20cry.%20Others%20imitated%20and%20soon%20about%20a%20thousand%20people%20joined%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20it%20happened!%20The%20moment%20of%20Jesus%E2%80%99%20birth!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20stood%20up%2C%20holding%20not%20a%20cloth%20doll%20but%20a%20real%20live%20baby%20in%20his%20arms!%20The%20crowd%20went%20wild.%20I%20lost%20my%20power%20of%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20later%20discovered%2C%20some%20of%20our%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20the%20shepherds%20to%20be%20precise%20%E2%80%93%20had%20discovered%20a%20baby%20behind%20the%20stage.%20It%20was%20the%20child%20of%20a%20woman%20labourer%20who%20along%20with%20others%20had%20been%20brought%20into%20the%20jail%20to%20do%20construction%20work.%20The%20actors%20had%20%E2%80%98borrowed%E2%80%99%20the%20baby%20and%20managed%20to%20pass%20it%20on%20to%20Mary%20and%20Joseph%20on%20stage.%20It%20was%20a%20defining%20moment%20in%20the%20drama.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20kings%20%E2%80%93%20dressed%20in%20Indian%20king%20costumes%20replete%20with%20Indian%20crowns%20and%20Indian%20beads%20%E2%80%93%20walked%20in%20and%20offered%20%E2%80%98gifts%20of%20gold%2C%20frankincense%20and%20myrrh%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20And%20as%20they%20knelt%20before%20Indian%20baby%20Jesus%2C%20the%20choir%20walked%20up%20on%20stage%2C%20surrounded%20the%20nativity%20scene%20and%20sang%20%E2%80%98Silent%20Night%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20will%20never%20forget%20the%20silence%20that%20followed.%20The%20Nigerian%20choir%20sang%20pitch-perfect.%20They%20were%20magical!%20Was%20this%20the%20same%20choir%20that%20had%20come%20to%20blows%20just%20days%20before%3F%20The%20actors%20joined%20in%20as%20did%20those%20few%20in%20the%20audience%20who%20knew%20the%20carol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSilent%20Night%2C%20Holy%20Night%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAll%20is%20calm%2C%20all%20is%20bright%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20they%20finished%20singing%2C%20a%20hush%20had%20fallen%20on%20the%20crowd.%20Some%20sort%20of%20heavenly%20peace%20had%20indeed%20descended%20on%20Jail%20No.%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20play%20ended%20and%20Nigel%20gave%20one%20last%20speech.%20It%20was%20halting%20and%20went%20something%20like%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFriends%2C%20I%20know%20Diwali%20was%20a%20difficult%20day%20for%20you.%20You%20wanted%20to%20spend%20it%20with%20your%20family%20but%20you%20spent%20it%20here%20in%20jail.%20This%20is%20my%20first%20Christmas%20away%20from%20home%20too.%20Mary%20and%20Joseph%20were%20far%20away%20from%20home%20too.%20In%20the%20company%20of%20strangers.%20And%20yet%2C%20they%20were%20not%20alone.%20Neither%20are%20we.%20Christmas%20reminds%20me%20that%20we%20are%20never%20alone%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20voice%20broke.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6.%20And%20when%20you%20think%20there%20is%20no%20hope%20left%2C%20something%20wonderful%20will%20happen.%20I%20know%20it%20will.%20And%20you%20will%20be%20given%20the%20strength%20to%20carry%20on.%20Tomorrow%20will%20be%20better%20than%20yesterday.%20Merry%20Christmas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20sun%20set%2C%20the%20crowd%20dispersed%20and%20started%20heading%20back%20to%20their%20barracks%20in%20high%20spirits.%20The%20actors%20laughed%2C%20hugged%20and%20congratulated%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20years%20have%20since%20passed.%20I%20lost%20touch%20with%20Nigel%20and%20his%20team%20after%20he%20got%20acquitted.%20But%20every%20December%20I%20remember%20the%20Tihar%20Theatre%20Troupe%20and%20give%20thanks%20for%20the%20memory%20of%20Christmas%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3ETales%20from%20the%20Jail%20%E2%80%93%20Christmas%20in%20Tihar%20and%20Other%20Stories%3Cem%3E%2C%20an%20anthology%20of%20a%20prison%20counsellor%E2%80%99s%20memoirs%20by%20Rohit%20Kumar.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703493025000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F25122227%2Fsaad-chaudhry-AqHIWSsF24I-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fchristmas-in-tihar%