%3EJamal%20and%20Habib%20were%20standing%20in%20a%20far%20corner%20at%20the%20back%20of%20the%20Press%20Club%20courtyard%2C%20watching%20the%20speakers%20at%20the%20Palestine%20protest.%20There%20were%20many%20empty%20chairs%2C%20but%20it%20was%20quiet%20at%20the%20back%2C%20where%20Jamal%20could%20smoke%20and%20have%20a%20parallel%20discussion%20on%20the%20event.%20They%20were%20there%20more%20in%20solidarity%2C%20less%20to%20actually%20listen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLook%20at%20the%20turn%20out!%20Nobody%20cares%20anymore%2C%20yaar.%20The%20same%2020%20people%20at%20every%20protest!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20are%20scared%20to%20come%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20becoming%20like%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20surveillance%2C%20jail%2C%20the%20average%20person%20overjoyed%20at%20the%20thought%20of%20Muslims%20being%20put%20in%20their%20place.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYes%20but%20Gaza%20is%20of%20a%20different%20order%2C%20Jamal%20bhai.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20men%20in%20servers%E2%80%99%20white%20uniforms%20carried%20out%20a%20rather%20modest%20steel%20urn%20and%20some%20paper%20cups%20and%20placed%20them%20on%20a%20side%20table%20near%20the%20entrance%2C%20across%20the%20breadth%20of%20the%20courtyard%20from%20where%20they%20had%20been%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20look%20at%20the%20amount%20of%20tea!%20It%20becomes%20less%20and%20less%20each%20time.%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20they%20ever%20have%20enough%20tea%20for%20everyone%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20like%20the%20place%20is%20teeming%20with%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20observed%20the%20steel%20container%20at%20the%20entrance%2C%20a%20woman%20slipped%20into%20the%20courtyard%20and%20into%20their%20line%20of%20vision.%20She%20surveyed%20the%20scene%20in%20the%20manner%20of%20a%20late%20entrant%2C%20and%20glancing%20hurriedly%20in%20all%20directions%20before%20she%20found%20her